      "name": "Skill",
      "args": {
        "skill": "stm32debug",
        "args": "SVD lookup STM32L476RG"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 debug svd-path STM32L476RG",
        "description": "Resolve SVD file path for STM32L476RG"
      }
    }
  ],
  "final_text": "The SVD file for the **STM32L476RG** was found via the **CubeIDE** source (highest-priority in the chain):\n\n```\nC:\\ST\\STM32CubeIDE_2.1.1\\STM32CubeIDE\\plugins\\\n  com.st.stm32cube.ide.mcu.productdb.debug_2.2.400.202601091600\\\n  resources\\cmsis\\STMicroelectronics_CMSIS_SVD\\\n  STM32L476.svd\n```\n\nNote that the SVD filename is `STM32L476.svd` \u2014 it covers the whole L476 family, not just the RG density variant. This file is what `stm32 debug read-peripheral` and `stm32 debug snapshot` use internally when targeting that device."
}